CustomField.description: This field is optional. Where an initial 10% federal income tax withholding is already presumed to apply to the transaction, this is the additional discretionary dollar amount, if any, over and above the baseline 10%, that the IRA plan owner or distribution recipient elects to have withheld from the distribution.
CustomField.inlineHelpText: The additional discretionary dollar amount of federal withholdings, over and above the baseline 10%, to the IRA plan.
CustomField.label: Additional Federal Withholdings
